gh','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-07 00:00:00',430,NULL),(1062,222,'ttt','M','no',0,14,2,2,0,4,'hi','hghgh','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-07 00:00:00',430,NULL),(1063,222,'ttt','M','no',0,18,2,2,0,4,'hi','hghgh','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-07 00:00:00',430,NULL),(1064,223,'Sign Up','M','no',0,1,1,1,0,1,'hi','Welcome to the #Organization Heart Discharge program powered by Quantified Care! If you ever have a question or concern about your surgery, please feel free to call us at 1-XXX-XXX-XXXX. If it is after 5 PM, a weekend, or a holiday, instead please call the Answering Service at XXX-XXX-XXXX. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',431,NULL),(1065,223,'Fill Rx & adherence','M','no',0,1,2,1,0,0,'hi','Your medication prescriptions were given to you when you left the hospital. Did you fill all your meds from the pharmacy? Call your doctor\'s office if you can\'t get your meds for some reason. Remember, taking your meds exactly as prescribed is the best way to start feeling better.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',432,NULL),(1066,223,'Med Organization','M','no',0,2,2,2,0,0,'hi','Make sure your medications are organized so that you are taking what you were discharged on, go through your old meds and put them aside. Try using a 7 day pillbox, which you can pick up at any pharmacy.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',432,NULL),(1067,223,'Rehab Appointment','M','no',0,2,5,2,0,0,'hi','You should have an appointment set up at the #Organization Rehab Clinic. The folks there will help you feel better and stay out of the hospital!? If you haven\'t received your appointment details please call XXX-XXX-XXXX to set one up. The Rehab Clinic is located at #Address. ?We\'re excited to see you there!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',435,NULL),(1068,223,'Weight Management','M','no',0,3,3,3,0,0,'hi','Remember to check your weight at the same time in the morning before you eat every day? Keep a log and report an overnight weight gain of greater than 2 lbs or a greater than 5 lbs gain in a week to your Doctor. It may be an indication that fluids are building up in your body. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',433,NULL),(1069,223,'Symptom Tracking 1','M','no',0,3,4,3,0,0,'hi','Did you know symptoms of heart disease may include pain in the chest, neck, jaw, or throat. Shortness of breath and fatigue with swelling in the feet, ankles, legs and/or abdomen are also common signs of heart disease. Be sure to tell your doctor immediately if you are having these symptoms.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',434,NULL),(1070,223,'Weight gain','M','no',0,4,3,4,0,0,'hi','Have you gained more than 3 lbs since your first day at home? If so, call your doctor\'s office, you may be retaining fluid, which can lead you back in the hospital.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',433,NULL),(1071,223,'Salt consumption','M','no',0,4,5,4,0,0,'hi','Did you know that you should consume no more than 2,000 mg of salt per day and less than 1,500 mg if possible? 1,500 mg is about 2/3 teaspoon of salt. Salt leads to fluid retention and  even one high salt meal can land you back in the hospital. Be careful and aware of the food you eat.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',435,NULL),(1072,223,'Control fluid intake','M','no',0,5,2,5,0,0,'hi','Medicines aren\'t the only way to control excess fluid retention - Along with taking your meds, it\'s recommended that you drink less than 2 liters of fluid a day. You can keep track of this by using a 2 Liter soda bottle!? Remember fluids include things like water, juice and soup.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',432,NULL),(1073,223,'Rehab Follow-up','M','no',0,5,5,5,0,0,'hi','Have you had your follow up visit at the #Organization Rehab Clinic to discuss your heart and recent hospitalization? If not, please call them at XXX-XXX-XXXX to make sure you are scheduled to be seen in the next 3 days. The Rehab Clinic can also give you IV Lasix to help with swelling.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',435,NULL),(1074,223,'Med complications','M','no',0,6,2,6,0,0,'hi','If you are having trouble with any of your discharge medications, let your medical team know. Continue to take the medications you were prescribed until your doctor tells you otherwise.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',432,NULL),(1075,223,'Low energy levels','M','no',0,6,4,6,0,0,'hi','Having low energy and feeling sad or depressed are common symptoms after leaving the hospital. Your energy level will slowly return and your mood should improve. If in the next week they do not, contact your nurse.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',434,NULL),(1076,223,'One week progress','M','no',0,7,1,7,0,0,'hi','You have been out of the hospital for one week! Remember to keep taking your medications, weigh yourself daily, limit your salt and fluid intake and see your doctor for follow up.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',431,NULL),(1077,223,'Symptom Tracking 2','M','no',0,7,4,7,0,0,'hi','Make sure to check your weight. Has your weight increased more than 5 lbs. this week? If so, let your Doctor know as soon as possible.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',434,NULL),(1078,223,'Stay out of the hospital 1','M','no',0,8,2,8,0,0,'hi','Take your heart medications as prescribed. This will help you stay out of the hospital and help you feel better. If you\'re using a pillbox remember to fill it for the week.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',432,NULL),(1079,223,'Symptom Tracking 3','M','no',0,9,4,9,0,0,'hi','If you are having trouble breaking at night, try resting with 2 pillows instead of one. This will help fluid that may be in your lungs to move further down your body. If this is still not helping, be sure to call your Doctor.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',434,NULL),(1080,223,'Heart failure explanation','M','no',0,9,1,9,0,0,'hi','You have a condition in which the heart is unable to pump enough blood and oxygen to meet the body\'s needs. When this happens, blood and fluid that should be pumped out of the heart backs up in the lungs and other parts of the body. This is why many people with heart failure have shortness of breath or swelling in the extremities. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',431,NULL),(1081,223,'Daily weight check','M','no',0,10,3,10,0,0,'hi','Have you been checking your weight daily? It is best to do it first thing in the morning each day. Make it a routine and log your results. It may seem like an annoying task, but it is the best sign of your health status. Try to see how many weight checks you can do in a row!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',433,NULL),(1082,223,'Limit fluid intake','M','no',0,10,5,10,0,0,'hi','Remember to limit your fluid intake to 6 to 9 cups or about 2 liters. When living with heart failure, your body has difficulty ridding itself of water and salt.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',435,NULL),(1083,223,'Do not skip medications','M','no',0,11,2,11,0,0,'hi','Diuretics, lasix or water pills will make you want to urinate, but please DO NOT use this as an excuse to skip your dose. This medication treats fluid retention, which can land you in the hospital.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',432,NULL),(1084,223,'Avoid heavy excercise','M','no',0,11,5,11,0,0,'hi','Walking is a good low-impact exercise. Check with your Doctor before starting an exercise program since overwork and fatigue should be avoided.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',435,NULL),(1085,223,'Symptom Tracking 4','M','no',0,12,4,12,0,0,'hi','Notify your doctor of worsening symptoms. Shortness of breath might mean that you have too much fluid in your body making your heart work harder and making it more difficult to breath.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',434,NULL),(1086,223,'Nutrition advice','M','no',0,13,5,13,0,0,'hi','You need to be very careful with your salt intake. Even one overly salty meal could land you in the hospital. Learn to read the nutritional labels on food products and look for the word sodium. Did you know that just one frozen dinner may have more sodium or salt (1,500mg) than you\'re allowed?!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',435,NULL),(1087,223,'Two week progress','M','no',0,14,1,14,0,0,'hi','Your at 2 weeks since you\'ve left the hospital! Congrats to you! Keep up the good work by taking your medications, checking your weight and restricting the amount of fluids & salt.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',431,NULL),(1088,223,'Regular weight check','M','no',0,14,3,14,0,0,'hi','How many weight checks have you done in a row?! Continue to stick with it, log your weights and make it part of your routine. If your weight increases greater than 2 lbs overnight or greater than 5 lbs gain in a week, call your doctor immediately.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',433,NULL),(1089,223,'Med Reminder','M','no',0,15,2,15,0,0,'hi','Remember to take your heart medications as prescribed. This will help you stay out of the hospital and help you feel better. If you\'re using a pillbox remember to fill it for the week.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',432,NULL),(1090,223,'DASH diet advice','M','no',0,16,5,16,0,0,'hi','Have you heard of the DASH diet? The DASH diet is highly recommended for people with heart conditions. It\'s actually ranked the #1 diet for 7th year in a row by US News & World Report. You can learn about it here:  http://bit.ly/1Elpg4a\nThere are lots of cookbooks and recipes online.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',435,NULL),(1091,223,'Symptom check 5','M','no',0,17,4,17,0,0,'hi','Symptoms to report to your doctor include worsening: chest pain, weight gain, swelling, fatigue or dizziness and shortness of breath. Call us at XXX-XXX-XXXX. We\'re here to help!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',434,NULL),(1092,223,'Resting advice','M','no',0,18,5,18,0,0,'hi','Go easy on yourself, even during exercise. Rest, take naps and take your time doing things. Heart failure is a condition in which the heart is no longer able to pump out enough oxygen-rich blood. This may cause you to feel fatigued and tired.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',435,NULL),(1093,223,'Weight check reminder','M','no',0,19,3,19,0,0,'hi','Just sending you a reminder to check your weight each morning at the same time, before you eat. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',433,NULL),(1094,223,'Three week progress','M','no',0,21,1,21,0,0,'hi','Congrats on the 3 week mark since your discharge! Keep up the great work.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',431,NULL),(1095,223,'Med Reminder 2','M','no',0,22,2,22,0,0,'hi','Have you been taking your medications? We know it can be hard, but it\'s incredibly important to continue to take them as prescribed.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',432,NULL),(1096,223,'Report symptoms','M','no',0,23,4,23,0,0,'hi','Symptoms to report to your doctor include worsening: chest pain, weight gain, swelling, fatigue or dizziness and shortness of breath. Call us at XXX-XXX-XXXX. We\'re here to help!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',434,NULL),(1097,223,'Prescription refill reminder','M','no',0,24,2,24,0,0,'hi','Your prescription should be running low. Make it a priority to refill your prescription before you run out! If you have any questions, please call us at XXX-XXX-XXXX.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',432,NULL),(1098,223,'Check weight gain ','M','no',0,25,3,25,0,0,'hi','Have you gained 5 lbs. or more in the last 7 days? If so, call your doctor. Continue to check your weight everyday.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',433,NULL),(1099,223,'Prescription refill follow-up','M','no',0,26,2,26,0,0,'hi','If you haven\'t already, please refill your prescription. It\'s important not to miss a dose.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',432,NULL),(1100,223,'Smoking cessation','M','no',0,28,4,28,0,0,'hi','If you smoke, stop smoking. Every puff increases your heart rate and blood pressure putting additional stress on your heart, while chemicals in tobacco can harm your blood cells. An easy way to improve your condition is to stop smoking.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',434,NULL),(1101,223,'Report symptoms 2','M','no',0,29,4,29,0,0,'hi','Symptoms to report to your doctor include worsening: chest pain, weight gain, swelling, fatigue or dizziness and shortness of breath. Call us at XXX-XXX-XXXX. We\'re here to help!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',434,NULL),(1102,223,'One month progress','M','no',0,30,1,30,0,0,'hi','It has been 1 month since you left the hospital! Congratulations for making it to the end of the #Organization Heart Discharge program! We hope these follow ups and educational reminders have been helpful in getting you back on track. After today you will not receive any more messages but please feel free to call us at  1-XXX-XXX-XXXX if you have any questions.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',431,NULL),(1103,224,'Sign Up','M','no',0,1,1,1,0,1,'hi','Welcome to the #Organization Spine Discharge program! If you ever have a question or concern about your surgery or medical care please feel free to call us at 1-800-981-5904 between the hours of 8AM-5PM. If it is after 5 PM, a weekend, or a holiday, instead please call the Orthopedic Resident at 410-351-8211.  If at any point you have a medical emergency call 911.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-10 00:00:00',436,NULL),(1104,224,'Fill Rx','M','no',0,1,2,1,0,0,'hi','Your medication prescription was given to you when you left the hospital. Did you fill all your meds from the pharmacy? Call your doctor\'s office if you can\'t get your meds for some reason. Remember, taking your meds exactly as prescribed is the best way to start feeling better.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',437,NULL),(1105,224,'Showering','M','no',0,1,3,1,0,0,'hi','Tomorrow you can shower with or without your surgical dressing on the incision. Do whichever you feel most comfortable with. After showering, pat the incision dry and apply a new, dry dressing to the incision.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',441,NULL),(1106,224,'Med Organization','M','no',0,2,2,2,0,0,'hi','Keep your medications organized. Try using a 7 day pillbox, which you can pick up at any pharmacy.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',437,NULL),(1107,224,'Symptom Check','M','no',0,2,4,2,0,0,'hi','Keep track of your symptoms. If you have a fever of 101.5 degrees F or higher, sweats, or chills, please call your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, call the On-call Resident at 410-351-8211. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',442,NULL),(1108,224,'Surgery explanation','M','no',0,3,1,3,0,0,'hi','We hope your recovery is going well. To recap the procedure, during your surgery your surgeon removed any bone spurs and a part of your lamina bone. This gives your spinal nerves more space and should relieve pressure.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',436,NULL),(1109,224,'Drainage @ incision','M','no',0,3,3,3,0,0,'hi','Some drainage from your surgical incision in the first few days is normal. Do not be concerned if the wound is slightly reddish-brown/yellow. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',441,NULL),(1110,224,'Dressing Advice','M','no',0,4,3,4,0,0,'hi','Make sure to keep your surgical dressing clean and dry. If your surgical dressing becomes wet, replace it with a dry surgical dressing once or twice a day as needed. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',441,NULL),(1111,224,'Avoid hospital trips','M','no',0,5,1,5,0,0,'hi','Please avoid trips back to the hospital if it is not an emergency.  If at anytime you are not receiving answers to any clinical questions or concern please call 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',436,NULL),(1112,224,'Symptom check 2','M','no',0,6,4,6,0,0,'hi','If you have any of the following symptoms, be sure to immediately call your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, call the On-call Resident at 410-351-8211: more redness, swelling, excessive drainage at the incision site, increasing pain despite rest and taking pain meds, new pain in arms or legs or new weakness, issues with urination or bowel movements.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',442,NULL),(1113,224,'1 week progress','M','no',0,7,1,7,0,0,'hi','You have been out of the hospital for one week! Remember to keep taking your medications as prescribed, keep up with your wound care and see your doctor for follow up.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',436,NULL),(1114,224,'Bandage removal','M','no',0,8,3,8,0,0,'hi','Your bandages should have fallen off or will fall off within the next couple of days. If they have not fallen off on their own, it is safe to remove them yourself.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',441,NULL),(1115,224,'Decrease in drainage','M','no',0,9,3,9,0,0,'hi','Drainage from your surgical incision should be decreasing over time, if it is not decreasing, please let us know by calling your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, calling the On-call Resident at 410-351-821. Do not put any creams on the incision unless you check with your doctor first.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',441,NULL),(1116,224,'Avoid hospital trips','M','no',0,10,1,10,0,0,'hi','Please avoid trips back to the hospital if it is not an emergency.  If at anytime you are not receiving answers to any clinical questions or concern please call 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',436,NULL),(1117,224,'Wound infections','M','no',0,10,4,10,0,0,'hi','Wound infections are most common at about 10 days after surgery. Call your doctor if you have any of these symptoms: fever (101.5 degrees F or higher), expanding redness at the incision site, increasing pain, change in the amount, appearance, or odour of drainage from the incision.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',442,NULL),(1118,224,'Medication complications','M','no',0,11,2,11,0,0,'hi','If you are having trouble with any of your discharge medications, let your medical team know.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',437,NULL),(1119,224,'2 week progress','M','no',0,14,1,14,0,0,'hi','It\'s been 2 weeks since your surgery. Good job! Take it easy and don\'t over work yourself.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',436,NULL),(1120,224,'Symptom check 3','M','no',0,14,4,14,0,0,'hi','It is important to still keep track of your symptoms. Call your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, call the On-call Resident at 410-351-8211 if you experience more redness, swelling, excessive drainage at the incision site, increasing pain despite rest and taking pain meds, new pain in arms or legs or new weakness, issues with urination or bowel movements.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',442,NULL),(1121,224,'Decrease in medication','M','no',0,15,2,15,0,0,'hi','Many patients wean themselves off of their pain medications over the course of 2-4 weeks.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',437,NULL),(1122,224,'Avoid hospital trips 3','M','no',0,17,1,17,0,0,'hi','Please avoid trips back to the hospital if it is not an emergency.  If at anytime you are not receiving answers to any clinical questions or concern please call 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',436,NULL),(1123,224,'3 week progress','M','no',0,21,1,21,0,0,'hi','Congrats on the 3 week mark since your surgery! Keep up the great work.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',436,NULL),(1124,224,'Limit activity','M','no',0,4,5,4,0,0,'hi','Now that you are back home, here are a few tips: (1) Try not sit for longer than 20 minutes at a time, (2) Bend from your knees and avoid bending at the waist,','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1125,224,'Resting advice','M','no',0,5,5,5,0,0,'hi','When lying down, use a firm mattress. When sitting down, avoid sitting on low couches and recliner chairs.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1126,224,'Avoid strenuous activity ','M','no',0,6,5,6,0,0,'hi','At this stage, it\'s important to avoid any strenuous or hard activities. For example, avoid lifting or carrying anything that weighs more than a milk carton. You can take short walks. This is a great way to build muscle and stamina, but stop as soon as your pain increases.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1127,224,'2 week visit reminder','M','no',0,7,5,7,0,0,'hi','Have you scheduled your 2-week post-op visit yet? If not, please call the Central Scheduling Office at 410-328-3330 to schedule your appointment. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1128,224,'Driving advice','M','no',0,8,5,8,0,0,'hi','Do not drive for at least another week. If you are a passenger, stop to stretch every 30-45 minutes. After two weeks have passed since your surgery, you can begin to make short trips. Remember not to ever drive when taking pain medication. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1129,224,'2 week visit reminder 2','M','no',0,9,5,9,0,0,'hi','This is a quick reminder that you should be going in for your 2-week post-op visit this week. If you have not yet scheduled your appointment or needs to change it for any reason, please call the Central Scheduling Office at 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1130,224,'Avoid heavy lifting','M','no',0,12,5,12,0,0,'hi','Continue to avoid heavy lifting. Limit lifting anything above 10 pounds. Make sure to avoid bending.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1131,224,'Begin sexual activity advice','M','no',0,16,5,16,0,0,'hi','Now that you are over two weeks into the recovery process, you can engage in sexual activity if it is not painful to do so.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1132,224,'Smoking Cessation','M','no',0,17,5,17,0,0,'hi','If you smoke, you should consider stopping. Smoking results in less blood circulation to your discs and spine. Reduced blood circulation can negatively affect healing.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1133,224,'Walking for excercise','M','no',0,19,5,19,0,0,'hi','Walking is an ideal exercise to be doing at this point. It\'s a good way to build muscle strength, but also great for your heart and lungs. Try slowly increasing the amount you walk, but make sure to  stop before it\'s painful. Don\'t push yourself.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1134,224,'Getting back to work','M','no',0,23,5,23,0,0,'hi','Recovery is a process. Stick with it! Getting back to work depends on your age, the extent of your surgery and how you are feeling. Consult your doctor before considering going back to work.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1135,224,'Recovery timeline','M','no',0,25,5,25,0,0,'hi','People generally go back to light work within 4-6 weeks after surgery. Talk with your doctor about when it might be right for you. Heavier work and sports may be appropriate after 2 to 3 months.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1136,224,'Physical Therapy & Recovery Timeline','M','no',0,27,5,27,0,0,'hi','Your doctor may recommend that you go to a physical therapy clinic starting around 6 weeks after surgery. You will need a prescription from your doctor. You can work with your insurance company to find a therapy clinic near you. Generally, physical therapy lasts about 4-6 weeks and full recovery takes about 4 months.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1137,224,'Benefits of physical therapy','M','no',0,29,5,29,0,0,'hi','Physical therapy will not only improve your health but also restore function and mobility. You will start slowly and focus on decreasing inflammation and pain.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',443,NULL),(1138,225,'Sign Up','M','no',0,1,1,1,0,1,'hi','Welcome to Quantified Care\'s High Blood Pressure Discharge program! If you ever have any questions or concerns during the program, feel free to call us at 1-XXX-XXX-XXXX. If it is after 5 PM, a weekend, or a holiday, instead please call our resident physician at XXX-XXX-XXXX. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',444,NULL),(1139,225,'Med Adherence','M','no',0,1,2,1,0,0,'hi','Your medication prescription was given to you when you left the hospital. Did you fill all your meds from the pharmacy? Call your doctor\'s office if you can\'t get your meds for some reason. Remember, taking your meds exactly as prescribed is a powerful way to prevent Americas number one killer. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',445,NULL),(1140,225,'BP Measurement technique','M','no',0,1,3,1,0,0,'hi','\"Make sure you are taking your blood pressure with the correct technique! Here\'s a link to step-by-step instructions on how to take your own blood pressure at home with pictures:http://www.heart.org/HEARTORG/Conditions/HighBloodPressure/KnowYourNumbers/Monitoring-Your-Blood-Pressure-at-Home_UCM_301874_Article.jsp#.WUu96xPyu9Y \n\"','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1141,225,'Med Organization','M','no',0,2,2,2,0,0,'hi','\"Keep your medications organized. Try using a 7 day pillbox, which you can pick up at any pharmacy.\n\"','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',445,NULL),(1142,225,'Right BP level','M','no',0,2,3,2,0,0,'hi','It is important that you take your blood pressure at home and record your results. If your blood pressure is below 120/80, you are on the right track. But if your blood pressure is above 140/90, this is considered Stage 1 hypertension and you should contact your doctor about other interventions.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1143,225,'BP Reminder','M','no',0,3,3,3,0,0,'hi','Don\'t forget to take your blood pressure daily! The reading on the blood pressure meter consists of a systolic blood pressure (upper number) and diastolic blood pressure (lower number). Systolic indicates how much pressure your blood is exerting against your artery walls when your heart beats and diastolic indicates how much pressure your blood is exerting while the heart is resting between beats.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1144,225,'Low sodium recipe','M','no',0,3,4,3,0,0,'hi','A way to keep your food flavourful while also cutting back on sodium is to season your food with herbs. You can find a recipe for low-sodium chicken here! http://goo.gl/mVtidg ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1145,225,'Lower Salt intake benefits','M','no',0,2,5,2,0,0,'hi','In order to control your blood pressure, you may have to limit your sodium (salt) intake. Salt causes increased fluid retention, weight gain, as well as increased blood pressure.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1146,225,'Med Reminder','M','no',0,4,2,4,0,0,'hi','Have you taken your medicine today? Take your medicine exactly as prescribed and try not to skip doses. Missing doses could cause your blood pressure to get out of control and put undue stress on your heart and blood vessels.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',445,NULL),(1147,225,'Food related tips','M','no',0,4,4,4,0,0,'hi','Make it a habit to read food labels. They contain information about sugar, fat, and salt that can help you make good food choices. The American Heart Association recommends no more than 2,300 milligrams (mgs) of salt a day and an ideal limit of no more than 1,500 mg per day for most adults.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1148,225,'Smoking Cessation','M','no',0,4,5,4,0,0,'hi','Smoking is the number one reversible risk factor. If you smoke, stop immediately. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1149,225,'Symptoms tracking','M','no',0,5,3,5,0,0,'hi','Hypertension does not usually manifest itself with symptoms but if there is a sudden jump in your blood pressure along with worsening symptoms, contact your doctor immediately and go to the ER. Also, visit the ER in the light of a hypertensive crisis (if your blood pressure is higher than 180/110).  If your blood pressure is abnormal, sit still for a few minutes to relax and measure again to make sure the reading is correct. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1150,225,'Delicious & Healthy foods','M','no',0,5,4,5,0,0,'hi','Delicious things can be healthy too! Perfect example is this recipe for spaghetti. See for yourself : http://dashdiet.org/spaghetti_sauce.asp','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1151,225,'Exercise routine','M','no',0,5,5,5,0,0,'hi','Start an exercise routine. Making exercise a habit can help lower your blood pressure. It can also give you more energy and is a great way to feel better. A great way to get started is to aim for 10,000 steps a day. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1152,225,'BP Reminder','M','no',0,6,3,6,0,0,'hi','Have you been checking your blood pressure regularly? Remember to record your readings in a notebook so that you can show your doctor at the follow up appointments.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1153,225,'Limit Sodium intake','M','no',0,6,4,6,0,0,'hi','Did you know that you should consume no more than 2,000mg of salt per day and less than 1,500 mg if possible? 1,500 mg is about 2/3 tsp of salt. Avoid high sodium intake by cutting down on processed foods.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1154,225,'1 week progress','M','no',0,7,1,7,0,0,'hi','Congratulations, you\'ve been out of the hospital for a week! Remember to keep taking your medications as prescribed and keep up with checking your blood pressure!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',444,NULL),(1155,225,'Symptoms tracking 2','M','no',0,7,3,7,0,0,'hi','If you are having a high blood pressure reading or a sudden increase in blood pressure along with symptoms and side effects, notify your doctor immediately.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1156,225,'Follow-up Visit','M','no',0,7,1,7,0,0,'hi','Have you scheduled a follow-up visit yet? If not, please call the office at XXX-XXX-XXXX to schedule your appointment. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',444,NULL),(1157,225,'Med Adherence','M','no',0,8,2,8,0,0,'hi','Good morning! Take out all the guesswork of taking your medications by correctly following the instructions prescribed by your doctor. You got this!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',445,NULL),(1158,225,'DASH diet','M','no',0,8,4,8,0,0,'hi','Follow the DASH diet and reduce your intake of fat, sodium, and alcohol which can all lead to an increase in your BP. For more information on the DASH diet, click here: http://www.heart.org/HEARTORG/Conditions/HighBloodPressure/MakeChangesThatMatter/Managing-Blood-Pressure-with-a-Heart-Healthy-Diet_UCM_301879_Article.jsp#.WUfsKhPyu9Y','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1159,225,'Food that lowers BP','M','no',0,9,4,9,0,0,'hi','Add blueberries, raspberries, strawberries to your cereal or shake! They contain flavonoids which are known to help lower blood pressure.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1160,225,'Workout Advice','M','no',0,9,5,9,0,0,'hi','The best things in life are meant to be shared! This includes working out - so find a workout buddy to help keep each other motivated and enjoyable.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1161,225,'Maintain BP Chart','M','no',0,10,3,10,0,0,'hi','Charting your blood pressure readings over weeks will help eliminate any false readings and give an accurate picture of your status.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1162,225,'Hidden sources of Sodium','M','no',0,10,4,10,0,0,'hi','Remember to also cut down on hidden sources of sodium such as bread, ice cream, and packaged foods.\n','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1163,225,'Stop Smoking','M','no',0,10,5,10,0,0,'hi','If you smoke, stop smoking.  Smoking kills.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1164,225,'Medication tips','M','no',0,11,2,11,0,0,'hi','Keep your medications where you will notice them. Try keeping Breakfast medicines in the kitchen away from moisture and Night time medicines by your nightstand.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',445,NULL),(1165,225,'Eating out tips','M','no',0,11,4,11,0,0,'hi','Eating out is also a hidden source of high salt intake. Request for your food to be prepared with less salt when you eat at restaurants . Dont Eat: Dried fruits preserved with sodium. Do Eat: Fresh and Canned Fruits!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1166,225,'Follow-up visit reminder','M','no',0,12,1,12,0,0,'hi','Did you remember to make an appointment to follow up with your doctor? If not, then call the scheduling center at XXX-XXX-XXXX!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',444,NULL),(1167,225,'Monitor BP Levels','M','no',0,12,3,12,0,0,'hi','The threshold for a normal BP is below 120/80. Pre-hypertension BP is 120-139/80-89. Hypertension Stage 1 BP is 140-159/90-99. Hypertension Stage 2 BP is higher than 160/100 which requires medical care. Remember to keep checking your blood pressure! We\'re almost at the end of two weeks.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1168,225,'Do\'s and Don\'ts','M','no',0,13,4,13,0,0,'hi','Don\'t Eat: Cured meats such as bacon, pepperoni, or hot dogs. Do Eat:  Fresh meat and turkey bacon!  Did you know that more than 75% of salt in the average American diet comes from salt added to processed foods like canned soups, fast food, and salad dressing? Make it a point to check the nutrition label.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1169,225,'2 week progress','M','no',0,14,1,14,0,0,'hi','\"\nYou\'ve made it to the end of two weeks! \n\"Believe that life is worth living and your belief will help create the fact.\"- William James','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',444,NULL),(1170,225,'Symptoms tracking 3','M','no',0,14,3,14,0,0,'hi','If you are having a high blood pressure reading, having symptoms, severe side effects or if your side effects are getting worse, notify your doctor immediately. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1171,226,'Sign Up','M','no',0,1,1,1,0,1,'hi','Hi #FN  you have been chosen to receive messages from the engage application.  To accept reply with Y, to decline reply with N','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',449,NULL),(1172,225,'Med Adherence','M','no',0,15,2,15,0,0,'hi','It\'s important to continue taking your medications! Symptoms are not common with hypertension but that does not mean you should skip doses.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',445,NULL),(1173,226,'test','M','no',0,2,2,2,0,4,'hi','sss','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',450,NULL),(1174,226,'test','M','no',0,6,2,2,0,4,'hi','sss','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',450,NULL),(1175,226,'test','M','no',0,10,2,2,0,4,'hi','sss','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',450,NULL),(1176,226,'test','M','no',0,14,2,2,0,4,'hi','sss','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',450,NULL),(1177,225,'Exercising tips  ','M','no',0,16,5,16,0,0,'hi','Working out 30 minutes daily with a modified diet ALONG with taking your medications is the best way to fight high BP. You could try walking on the treadmill or playing a sport you enjoy.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1178,225,'BP Reminder','M','no',0,17,3,17,0,0,'hi','Make sure to continue taking your blood pressure! Usually if your systolic blood pressure is below 120 and your diastolic blood pressure is below 80, you\'re on the right track!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1179,225,'Low Sodium receipe','M','no',0,17,4,17,0,0,'hi','Did you ever think Mac&Cheese could be made to be low in sodium? Check it out: https://recipes.heart.org/recipes/1025/bacon-mushroom-mac-and-cheese ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1180,225,'Healthy & tasty substitutes','M','no',0,18,4,18,0,0,'hi','There are healthy substitutes for your favourite foods that taste just as good. All you have to do is look! Pick up a healthy recipes book or look online. https://recipes.heart.org/','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1181,225,'Alcohol intake','M','no',0,18,5,18,0,0,'hi','Try to limit your alcohol intake. Mixing alcohol and medications can cause nausea, diarrhea and may put you at risk for harmful or adverse effects.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1182,225,'Workout Caution!','M','no',0,19,5,19,0,0,'hi','Remember that its a marathon and not a race. Gradually work your way up when exercising. Speak to your doctor about designing a workout plan that is best for you.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1183,225,'Calibrate your device','M','no',0,20,3,20,0,0,'hi','If you\'re using an automated blood pressure device, ensure that the device is calibrated and you\'re using an appropriate cuff size. A cuff that is too small can indicate higher than normal readings.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1184,225,'Healthy cottage cheese substitute','M','no',0,20,4,20,0,0,'hi','Love cottage cheese? One cup-serving can contain about 1000 mg of sodium. Look for alternatives such as greek yogurt as worthy substitute!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1185,225,'3 week progress','M','no',0,21,1,21,0,0,'hi','Great job making it to the end of 3 weeks! Keep taking your medication just as described.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',444,NULL),(1186,225,'Eating smart & healthy','M','no',0,21,4,21,0,0,'hi','Its important to remember that eating with hypertension isnt about food deprivation. Instead, its about eating smart and healthy for your body.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1187,225,'Maintain BP chart','M','no',0,22,3,22,0,0,'hi','Charting your blood pressure readings over time will help eliminate any false readings and give an accurate picture of your status.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1188,225,'Walking for exercise','M','no',0,23,5,23,0,0,'hi','Walking is a good low-impact exercise. Check with your doctor to see what exercise program is best for you.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1189,225,'Med Tracking','M','no',0,24,2,24,0,0,'hi','Keep track of your medication refill dates on a calendar. This will ensure you don\'t go without your medications, especially if you will be traveling.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',445,NULL),(1190,225,'Symptoms Tracking','M','no',0,25,3,25,0,0,'hi','Make sure to follow-up with your Doctor to report any new symptoms.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1191,225,'Med Adherence','M','no',0,26,2,26,0,0,'hi','Be sure to continue to take your prescription according to the doctors instructions!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',445,NULL),(1192,225,'BP Reminder','M','no',0,27,3,27,0,0,'hi','Remember to check your blood pressure daily!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1193,225,'High Potassium Diet','M','no',0,27,4,27,0,0,'hi','Go bananas for bananas! They are a source of potassium, which is essential in balancing sodium!','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1194,225,'Foods that heal','M','no',0,28,4,28,0,0,'hi','You know what one food is that reduces appetite and increases metabolism? Quinoa! Not only does it help in weight loss, but it also has many nutrients that the body needs to fight disease and help repair itself. Make sure you check out some delicious recipes using Quinoa! http://goo.gl/SEnspU','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',447,NULL),(1195,225,'Enjoy your workout','M','no',0,28,5,28,0,0,'hi','The goal of exercising is picking an activity you enjoy doing! This could be jogging, playing basketball, gardening, brisk walking or anything that raises your heart rate for a bit.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1196,225,'Symptoms Tracking','M','no',0,29,3,29,0,0,'hi','Remember to keep track of your symptoms and blood pressure! If you feel lightheaded or have shortness of breath, contact your doctor at XXX-XXX-XXXX.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',446,NULL),(1197,225,'Managing BP advice','M','no',0,29,5,29,0,0,'hi','To help control blood pressure, choose a diet that is low in fat and salt, maintain a healthy weight, exercise at least 30 minutes most days, and stop smoking.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1198,225,'1 Month Progress','M','no',0,30,1,30,0,0,'hi','You\'ve made it to the end of a month! Great work! \n\"We are never tired, so long as we can see far enough.\" - Ralph Waldo Emerson','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',444,NULL),(1199,225,'Routine Follow-up','M','no',0,30,5,30,0,0,'hi','Be sure to follow-up with your doctor at least every 2 months, watch your weight and modify your diet to reduce sodium and high fat content.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',448,NULL),(1200,227,'Sign Up','M','no',0,1,1,1,0,1,'hi','Welcome to the UMMC Spine Discharge program! If you ever have a question or concern about your surgery or medical care please feel free to call us at 1-800-981-5904 between the hours of 8AM-5PM. If it is after 5 PM, a weekend, or a holiday, instead please call the Orthopedic Resident at 410-351-8211.  If at any point you have a medical emergency call 911.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',451,NULL),(1201,228,'Sign Up','M','no',0,1,1,1,0,1,'hi','Hi #FN  you have been chosen to receive messages from the engage application.  To accept reply with Y, to decline reply with N','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',453,NULL),(1202,227,'Fill Rx & adherence','M','no',0,1,2,1,0,0,'hi','Your medication prescription was given to you when you left the hospital. Did you fill all your meds from the pharmacy? Call your doctor\'s office if you can\'t get your meds for some reason. Remember, taking your meds exactly as prescribed is the best way to start feeling better.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',452,NULL),(1203,227,'Showering','M','no',0,1,3,1,0,0,'hi','Today you can shower with or without your surgical dressing on the incision. Do whichever you feel most comfortable with. After showering, pat the incision dry and apply a new, dry dressing to the incision.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',454,NULL),(1204,228,'sas','M','no',0,2,2,2,0,3,'hi','asas','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',457,NULL),(1205,228,'sas','M','no',0,5,2,2,0,3,'hi','asas','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',457,NULL),(1206,228,'sas','M','no',0,8,2,2,0,3,'hi','asas','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',457,NULL),(1207,227,'Med Organization','M','no',0,2,2,2,0,0,'hi','Keep your medications organized. Try using a 7 day pillbox, which you can pick up at any pharmacy.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',452,NULL),(1208,227,'Symptom Check','M','no',0,2,4,2,0,0,'hi','Keep track of your symptoms. If you have a fever of 101.5 degrees F or higher, sweats, or chills, please call your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, call the On-call Resident at 410-351-8211. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',455,NULL),(1209,227,'Surgery Explanation','M','no',0,3,2,3,0,0,'hi','We hope your recovery is going well. To recap the procedure, during your surgery sections of your spine were fused together to decrease movement in certain areas that might have been inflamed or injured. This should stop harm to your nerves and decrease pain.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',452,NULL),(1210,227,'Drainage @ Incision','M','no',0,3,3,3,0,0,'hi','Some drainage from your surgical incision in the first few days is normal. Do not be concerned if the wound is slightly reddish-brown/yellow. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',454,NULL),(1211,227,'Surgical Dressing Advice','M','no',0,4,3,4,0,0,'hi','Make sure to keep your surgical dressing clean and dry. If your surgical dressing becomes wet, replace it with a dry surgical dressing once or twice a day as needed. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',454,NULL),(1212,227,'Avoid Hospital trips','M','no',0,4,1,4,0,0,'hi','Please avoid trips back to the hospital if it is not an emergency.  If at anytime you are not receiving answers to any clinical questions or concern please call 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',451,NULL),(1213,227,'Symptom check 2','M','no',0,6,4,6,0,0,'hi','If you have any of the following symptoms, be sure to immediately call your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, call the On-call Resident at 410-351-8211: more redness, swelling, excessive drainage at the incision site, increasing pain despite rest and taking pain meds, new pain in arms or legs or new weakness, issues with urination or bowel movements.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',455,NULL),(1214,227,'1 week progress','M','no',0,7,1,7,0,0,'hi','You have been out of the hospital for one week! Remember to keep taking your medications as prescribed, keep up with your wound care and see your doctor for follow up.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',451,NULL),(1215,227,'Bandage Removal','M','no',0,8,3,8,0,0,'hi','Your bandages should have fallen off or will fall off within the next couple of days. If they have not fallen off on their own, it is safe to remove them yourself.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',454,NULL),(1216,227,'Decrease in drainage','M','no',0,9,3,9,0,0,'hi','Drainage from your surgical incision should be decreasing over time, if it is not decreasing, please let us know by calling your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, calling the On-call Resident at 410-351-821. Do not put any creams on the incision unless you check with your doctor first.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',454,NULL),(1217,227,'Avoid Hospital trips 2','M','no',0,10,1,10,0,0,'hi','Please avoid trips back to the hospital if it is not an emergency.  If at anytime you are not receiving answers to any clinical questions or concern please call 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',451,NULL),(1218,227,'Wound Infections','M','no',0,10,3,10,0,0,'hi','Wound infections are most common at about 10 days after surgery. Call your doctor if you have any of these symptoms: fever (101.5 degrees F or higher), expanding redness at the incision site, increasing pain, change in the amount, appearance, or odor of drainage from the incision.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',454,NULL),(1219,227,'Medication Complications','M','no',0,11,2,11,0,0,'hi','If you are having trouble with any of your discharge medications, let your medical team know.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',452,NULL),(1220,227,'2 Week Progress','M','no',0,14,1,14,0,0,'hi','It\'s been 2 weeks since your surgery. Good job! Take it easy and don\'t over work yourself.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',451,NULL),(1221,227,'Symptom Check 3','M','no',0,14,4,14,0,0,'hi','It is important to still keep track of your symptoms. Call your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, call the On-call Resident at 410-351-8211 if you experience more redness, swelling, excessive drainage at the incision site, increasing pain despite rest and taking pain meds, new pain in arms or legs or new weakness, issues with urination or bowel movements.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',455,NULL),(1222,227,'Decrease Medication','M','no',0,15,2,15,0,0,'hi','Many patients wean themselves off of their pain medications over the course of 2-4 weeks.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',452,NULL),(1223,227,'Avoid Hospital trips 3','M','no',0,17,1,17,0,0,'hi','Please avoid trips back to the hospital if it is not an emergency.  If at anytime you are not receiving answers to any clinical questions or concern please call 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',451,NULL),(1224,227,'3 week progress','M','no',0,21,1,21,0,0,'hi','Congrats on the 3 week mark since your surgery! Keep up the great work.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',451,NULL),(1225,227,'Avoid Hospital trips','M','no',0,25,1,25,0,0,'hi','Please avoid trips back to the hospital if it is not an emergency.  If at anytime you are not receiving answers to any clinical questions or concern please call 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',451,NULL),(1226,229,'Sign Up','M','no',0,1,1,1,0,1,'hi','Hi #FN  you have been chosen to receive messages from the engage application.  To accept reply with Y, to decline reply with N','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',458,NULL),(1227,227,'Program Complete','M','no',0,30,1,30,0,0,'hi','It has been 1 month since your surgery. Congratulations for making it to the end of the UMMC Spine Discharge program! We hope these follow ups and educational reminders have been helpful in getting you back on track since your spine surgery. After today you will not receive any more messages but please feel free to call us at  410-328-3330 if you have any questions.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',451,NULL),(1228,229,'asa','M','no',0,2,2,2,0,3,'hi','Za','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',459,NULL),(1229,229,'asa','M','no',0,5,2,2,0,3,'hi','Za','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',459,NULL),(1230,229,'asa','M','no',0,8,2,2,0,3,'hi','Za','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',459,NULL),(1231,229,'asa','M','no',0,11,2,2,0,3,'hi','Za','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',459,NULL),(1232,227,'Limit Activity','M','no',0,4,5,4,0,0,'hi','Now that you are back home, here are a few tips: (1) Try not sit for longer than 20 minutes at a time, (2) Bend from your knees and avoid bending at the waist,','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1233,227,'Resting Advice','M','no',0,5,5,5,0,0,'hi','When lying down, use a firm mattress. When sitting down, avoid sitting on low couches and recliner chairs.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1234,227,'Avoid Strenuous advice','M','no',0,6,5,6,0,0,'hi','At this stage, it\'s important to avoid any strenuous or hard activities. For example, avoid lifting or carrying anything that weighs more than a milk carton. You can take short walks. This is a great way to build muscle and stamina, but stop as soon as your pain increases.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1235,227,'2 week visit reminder','M','no',0,7,5,7,0,0,'hi','Have you scheduled your 2-week post-op visit yet? If not, please call the Central Scheduling Office at 410-328-3330 to schedule your appointment. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1236,230,'Sign Up','M','no',0,1,1,1,0,1,'hi','Hi #FN  you have been chosen to receive messages from the engage application.  To accept reply with Y, to decline reply with N','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',460,NULL),(1237,227,'Driving Advice','M','no',0,8,5,8,0,0,'hi','Do not drive for at least another week. If you are a passenger, stop to stretch every 30-45 minutes. After two weeks have passed since your surgery, you can begin to make short trips. Remember not to ever drive when taking pain medication. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1238,230,'asas','M','no',0,2,2,2,0,3,'hi','Sas','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',461,NULL),(1239,230,'asas','M','no',0,5,2,2,0,3,'hi','Sas','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',461,NULL),(1240,230,'asas','M','no',0,8,2,2,0,3,'hi','Sas','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',461,NULL),(1241,227,'2 Week visit reminder 2','M','no',0,9,5,9,0,0,'hi','This is a quick reminder that you should be going in for your 2-week post-op visit this week. If you have not yet scheduled your appointment or needs to change it for any reason, please call the Central Scheduling Office at 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1242,227,'Avoid Heavy lifting','M','no',0,12,5,12,0,0,'hi','Continue to avoid heavy lifting. Limit lifting anything above 10 pounds. Make sure to avoid bending.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1243,227,'Begin Sexual Activity advice','M','no',0,16,5,16,0,0,'hi','Now that you are over two weeks into the recovery process, you can engage in sexual activity if it is not painful to do so.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1244,227,'Smoking Cessation','M','no',0,17,5,17,0,0,'hi','If you smoke, you should consider stopping. Smoking results in less blood circulation to your discs and spine. Reduced blood circulation can negatively affect healing.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1245,227,'Walking for exercise','M','no',0,19,5,19,0,0,'hi','Walking is an ideal exercise to be doing at this point. It\'s a good way to build muscle strength, but also great for your heart and lungs. Try slowly increasing the amount you walk, but make sure to  stop before it\'s painful. Don\'t push yourself.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1246,227,'Getting back to work','M','no',0,23,5,23,0,0,'hi','Recovery is a process. Stick with it! Getting back to work depends on your age, the extent of your surgery and how you are feeling. Consult your doctor before considering going back to work.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1247,227,'Getting back to work 2','M','no',0,25,5,25,0,0,'hi','If you are young, in good health, or your job is not very strenuous, you can expect to go back to work within 4-6 weeks. If you are older or your work is strenuous, returning to work may take 4-6 months. Talk with your doctor about when it might be right for you.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1248,227,'Physical Therapy & recovery timeline ','M','no',0,27,5,27,0,0,'hi','Your doctor may recommend that you go to a physical therapy clinic starting around 6 weeks after surgery. You will need a prescription from your doctor. You can work with your insurance company to find a therapy clinic near you. Generally, physical therapy lasts about 4-6 weeks and full recovery takes about 4 months.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1249,227,'Benefits of Physical Activity','M','no',0,29,5,29,0,0,'hi','Physical therapy will not only improve your health but also restore function and mobility. You will start slowly and focus on decreasing inflammation and pain.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',456,NULL),(1250,231,'Sign Up','M','no',0,1,1,1,0,1,'hi','Welcome to the UMMC Spine Discharge program! If you ever have a question or concern about your surgery or medical care please feel free to call us at 1-800-981-5904 between the hours of 8AM-5PM. If it is after 5 PM, a weekend, or a holiday, instead please call the Orthopedic Resident at 410-351-8211.  If at any point you have a medical emergency call 911.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',462,NULL),(1251,231,'Fill Rx & adherence','M','no',0,1,2,1,0,0,'hi','Your medication prescription was given to you when you left the hospital. Did you fill all your meds from the pharmacy? Call your doctor\'s office if you can\'t get your meds for some reason. Remember, taking your meds exactly as prescribed is the best way to start feeling better.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',463,NULL),(1252,231,'Showering','M','no',0,1,3,1,0,0,'hi','Tomorrow you can shower with or without your surgical dressing on the incision. Do whichever you feel most comfortable with. After showering, pat the incision dry and apply a new, dry dressing to the incision.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',464,NULL),(1253,231,'Med Organization','M','no',0,2,2,2,0,0,'hi','Keep your medications organized. Try using a 7 day pillbox, which you can pick up at any pharmacy.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',463,NULL),(1254,231,'Symptom Check','M','no',0,2,4,2,0,0,'hi','Keep track of your symptoms. If you have a fever of 101.5 degrees F or higher, sweats, or chills, please call your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, call the On-call Resident at 410-351-8211. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',465,NULL),(1255,231,'Surgery Explanation','M','no',0,3,1,3,0,0,'hi','We hope your recovery is going well. To recap the procedure, during your surgery your surgeon removed a part of a disc in your spine. This should relieve pressure on your spinal nerves and decrease your symptoms long-term. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',462,NULL),(1256,231,'Drainage @ Incision','M','no',0,3,3,3,0,0,'hi','Some drainage from your surgical incision in the first few days is normal. Do not be concerned if the wound is slightly reddish-brown/yellow. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',464,NULL),(1257,231,'Surgical Dressing Advice','M','no',0,4,3,4,0,0,'hi','Make sure to keep your surgical dressing clean and dry. If your surgical dressing becomes wet, replace it with a dry surgical dressing once or twice a day as needed. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',464,NULL),(1258,231,'Avoid Hospital Trips','M','no',0,5,1,5,0,0,'hi','Please avoid any trips back to the hospital.  If at anytime you are not receiving answers to any clinical questions or concerns please call 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',462,NULL),(1259,231,'Pain Management','M','no',0,5,4,5,0,0,'hi','You may still feel some pain, weakness or numbness from the surgery, but this should get better in a few weeks.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',465,NULL),(1260,231,'Symptom Check 2','M','no',0,6,4,6,0,0,'hi','If you have any of the following symptoms, be sure to immediately call your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, call the On-call Resident at 410-351-8211: more redness, swelling, excessive drainage at the incision site, increasing pain despite rest and taking pain meds, new pain in arms or legs or new weakness, issues with urination or bowel movements. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',465,NULL),(1261,