1,'Smoking Cessation','M','no',0,17,5,17,0,0,'hi','If you smoke, you should consider stopping. Smoking results in less blood circulation to your discs and spine. Reduced blood circulation can negatively affect healing.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',466,NULL),(1282,231,'Walking for Exercise','M','no',0,19,5,19,0,0,'hi','Walking is an ideal exercise to be doing at this point. It\'s a good way to build muscle strength, but also great for your heart and lungs. Try slowly increasing the amount you walk, but make sure to  stop before it\'s painful. Don\'t push yourself.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',466,NULL),(1283,231,'Heavy Activity timeline','M','no',0,20,5,20,0,0,'hi','Don\'t try to push yourself too much. Rehab takes time. Start heavy activities and sports after 2-3 months from surgery.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',466,NULL),(1284,231,'Continue Light Excecise','M','no',0,23,5,23,0,0,'hi','By now, your soft tissue has likely healed. Continue engaging in light exercise or back strengthening exercises if your doctor has recommended them.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',466,NULL),(1285,231,'Increase Activity','M','no',0,25,5,25,0,0,'hi','Gradually increase how much you walk each day, ride in the car, and  engage in housework while always being careful not to overexert yourself.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',466,NULL),(1286,231,'Physical Therapy & Recovery timeline','M','no',0,27,5,27,0,0,'hi','Your doctor may recommend that you go to a physical therapy clinic starting around 6 weeks after surgery. You will need a prescription from your doctor. You can work with your insurance company to find a therapy clinic near you. Generally, physical therapy lasts about 4-6 weeks and full recovery takes about 4 months.','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-11 00:00:00',466,NULL),(1287,231,'Benefits of Physical Therapy','M','no',0,29,5,29,0,0,'hi','Physical therapy will 