n.  To accept reply with Y, to decline reply with N','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',255,'no',1498835439366),(147,147,37,480,'2017-06-30',0,'New Patient Intro','M',1,'2017-06-30','sent','2017-06-30',2,1,0,0,'hi','Welcome to the Spine Discharge program! If you ever have a question or concern about your surgery or medical care please feel free to call us at 1-800-981-5904 between the hours of 8AM-5PM. If it is after 5 PM, a weekend, or a holiday, instead please call the Orthopedic Resident at 410-351-8211.  If at any point you have a medical emergency call 911.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',256,'no',1498835455167),(148,147,37,482,'2017-06-30',0,'Fill Rx & Adherence','M',1,'2017-06-30','sent','2017-06-30',3,1,0,0,'hi','Your medication prescription was given to you when you left the hospital. Did you fill all your meds from the pharmacy? Call your doctor\'s office if you can\'t get your meds for some reason. Remember, taking your meds exactly as prescribed is the best way to start feeling better.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',257,'no',1498835455451),(149,147,37,483,'2017-06-30',0,'Showering','M',1,'2017-06-30','sent','2017-06-30',3,1,0,0,'hi','Today you can shower with or without your surgical dressing on the incision. Do whichever you feel most comfortable with. After showering, pat the incision dry and apply a new, dry dressing to the incision.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',257,'no',1498835455757),(150,147,37,484,'2017-07-01',0,'Med Organization','M',2,'2017-07-01','sent','2017-06-30',3,2,0,0,'hi','Keep your medications organized. Try using a 7 day pillbox, which you can pick up at any pharmacy.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',257,'no',1498914000496),(151,147,37,485,'2017-07-01',0,'Symptom Check','M',2,'2017-07-01','sent','2017-06-30',4,2,0,0,'hi','Keep track of your symptoms. If you have a fever of 101.5 degrees F or higher, sweats, or chills, please call your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, call the On-call Resident at 410-351-8211. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',258,'no',1498914000753),(152,147,37,487,'2017-07-02',0,'Surgery Explanation','M',3,'2017-07-02','scheduled','2017-06-30',2,3,0,0,'hi','We hope your recovery is going well. To recap the procedure, during your surgery sections of your spine were fused together to decrease movement in certain areas that might have been inflamed or injured. This should stop harm to your nerves and decrease pain.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',256,'no',0),(153,147,37,488,'2017-07-02',0,'Drainage @ Incision','M',3,'2017-07-02','scheduled','2017-06-30',3,3,0,0,'hi','Some drainage from your surgical incision in the first few days is normal. Do not be concerned if the wound is slightly reddish-brown/yellow. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',257,'no',0),(154,147,37,489,'2017-07-03',0,'Surgical Dressing Advice','M',4,'2017-07-03','scheduled','2017-06-30',3,4,0,0,'hi','Make sure to keep your surgical dressing clean and dry. If your surgical dressing becomes wet, replace it with a dry surgical dressing once or twice a day as needed. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',257,'no',0),(155,147,37,490,'2017-07-04',0,'Avoid Hospital Trips','M',5,'2017-07-04','scheduled','2017-06-30',2,5,0,0,'hi','Please avoid trips back to the hospital if it is not an emergency.  If at anytime you are not receiving answers to any clinical questions or concern please call 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',256,'no',0),(156,147,37,492,'2017-07-05',0,'Symptom Check 2','M',6,'2017-07-05','scheduled','2017-06-30',4,6,0,0,'hi','If you have any of the following symptoms, be sure to immediately call your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, call the On-call Resident at 410-351-8211: more redness, swelling, excessive drainage at the incision site, increasing pain despite rest and taking pain meds, new pain in arms or legs or new weakness, issues with urination or bowel movements.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',258,'no',0),(157,147,37,494,'2017-07-06',0,'1 Week Progress','M',7,'2017-07-06','scheduled','2017-06-30',2,7,0,0,'hi','You have been out of the hospital for one week! Remember to keep taking your medications as prescribed, keep up with your wound care and see your doctor for follow up.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',256,'no',0),(158,147,37,496,'2017-07-03',0,'Limit Activity','M',4,'2017-07-03','scheduled','2017-06-30',4,4,0,0,'hi','Now that you are back home, here are a few tips: (1) Try not sit for longer than 20 minutes at a time, (2) Bend from your knees and avoid bending at the waist, (3) Only take short walks for the first 2 weeks.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',258,'no',0),(159,147,37,497,'2017-07-04',0,'Resting Advice','M',5,'2017-07-04','scheduled','2017-06-30',4,5,0,0,'hi','When lying down, use a firm mattress. When sitting down, avoid sitting on low couches and recliner chairs.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',258,'no',0),(160,147,37,499,'2017-07-05',0,'Avoid Strenuous Activity','M',6,'2017-07-05','scheduled','2017-06-30',4,6,0,0,'hi','At this stage, it\'s important to avoid any strenuous or hard activities. For example, avoid lifting or carrying anything that weighs more than a milk carton. You can take short walks. This is a great way to build muscle and stamina, but stop as soon as your pain increases.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',258,'no',0),(161,147,37,501,'2017-07-06',0,'2 Week Visit Reminder','M',7,'2017-07-06','scheduled','2017-06-30',5,7,0,0,'hi','Have you scheduled your 2-week post-op visit yet? If not, please call the Central Scheduling Office at 410-328-3330 to schedule your appointment. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',260,'no',0),(162,147,37,502,'2017-07-07',0,'Driving Advice','M',8,'2017-07-07','scheduled','2017-06-30',4,8,0,0,'hi','Do not drive for at least another week. If you are a passenger, stop to stretch every 30-45 minutes. After two weeks have passed since your surgery, you can begin to make short trips. Remember not to ever drive when taking pain medication. ','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',258,'no',0),(163,147,37,504,'2017-07-08',0,'2 Week Visit Reminder 2','M',9,'2017-07-08','scheduled','2017-06-30',5,9,0,0,'hi','This is a quick reminder that you should be going in for your 2-week post-op visit this week. If you have not yet scheduled your appointment or needs to change it for any reason, please call the Central Scheduling Office at 410-328-3330.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',260,'no',0),(164,147,37,506,'2017-07-11',0,'Avoid Heavy Lifting','M',12,'2017-07-11','scheduled','2017-06-30',4,12,0,0,'hi','Continue to avoid heavy lifting. Limit lifting anything above 10 pounds. Make sure to avoid bending.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',258,'no',0),(165,147,37,508,'2017-07-09',0,'Bandage Removal','M',10,'2017-07-09','scheduled','2017-06-30',3,10,0,0,'hi','Your bandages should have fallen off or will fall off within the next couple of days. If they have not fallen off on their own, it is safe to remove them yourself.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',257,'no',0),(166,147,37,509,'2017-07-10',0,'Decrease in Drainage','M',11,'2017-07-10','scheduled','2017-06-30',3,11,0,0,'hi','Drainage from your surgical incision should be decreasing over time, if it is not decreasing, please let us know by calling your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, calling the On-call Resident at 410-351-821. Do not put any creams on the incision unless you check with your doctor first.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',257,'no',0),(167,147,37,510,'2017-07-09',0,'Wound Infections','M',10,'2017-07-09','scheduled','2017-06-30',4,10,0,0,'hi','Wound infections are most common at about 10 days after surgery. Call your doctor if you have any of these symptoms: fever (101.5 degrees F or higher), expanding redness at the incision site, increasing pain, change in the amount, appearance, or odor of drainage from the incision.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',258,'no',0),(168,147,37,511,'2017-07-10',0,'Med Complications','M',11,'2017-07-10','scheduled','2017-06-30',3,11,0,0,'hi','If you are having trouble with any of your discharge medications, let your medical team know.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',257,'no',0),(169,147,37,513,'2017-07-13',0,'2 Week Progress','M',14,'2017-07-13','scheduled','2017-06-30',2,14,0,0,'hi','It\'s been 2 weeks since your surgery. Good job! Take it easy and don\'t over work yourself.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',256,'no',0),(170,147,37,515,'2017-07-13',0,'Symptom Check 3','M',14,'2017-07-13','scheduled','2017-06-30',4,14,0,0,'hi','It is important to still keep track of your symptoms. Call your Transition Specialist at 1-800-981-5904 or if after 5pm, call the On-call Resident at 410-351-8211 if you experience more redness, swelling, excessive drainage at the incision site, increasing pain despite rest and taking pain meds, new pain in arms or legs or new weakness, issues with urination or bowel movements.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',258,'no',0),(171,147,37,520,'2017-07-12',0,'Decrease Medications','M',13,'2017-07-12','scheduled','2017-06-30',3,13,0,0,'hi','Many patients wean themselves off of their pain medications over the course of 2-4 weeks.','no message','no message','Y','2017-06-30 15:10:39',257,'no',0),(172,220,39,1039,'2017-07-02',0,'Sign Up','M',1,'2017-07-02','sent','2017-07-02',1,1,0,1,'hi','Hi #FN  you have been chosen to receive messages from the engage application.  To accept reply with Y, to decline reply with N','no message','no message','Y','2017-07-02 04:00:06',422,'no',